post_text: Shoutout to Nellie and Arlene from Herrera Elementary School for creating a student led service team called Cancer Fighters! They have have been routinely creating care packages for local first responders and hospitals. As of this post, these student leaders have donated 8 boxes of pizza to St. Mary’s and 12 boxes of pizza to Millers Children’s Hospital, along with 94 Easter bags and 90 handmade bracelets. They have also created 49 to-go packages for first responders during the COVID19 pandemic. We are so proud of these two young ladies and all their service to the community! WE ARE #ProudtobeLBUSD

post_text:
#ThrowbackThursday Memo from Superintendent Stephens to LBUSD Principals, Jan. 17, 1919 “You are notified to close the schools of the City of Long Beach Friday, January 17, 1919, same to remain closed until further notice. This action is taken in order to try and stamp out the spread of the epidemic of influenza now existing in our city. Thanking you for your cooperation in the past and trusting that we may receive the same in the future, we beg to remain.”
-Ralph L. Taylor, M.D. Health Officer
#throwback #LBSchoolsHistory #LongBeachStrong #SocialDistancing #proudtobeLBUSD

post_text:
⛑School Closure Extended Through at Least May 3 (El Cierre de Escuelas se extiende al menos hasta el 3 de mayo)⛑ The closure of all Long Beach Unified School District Schools will extend through at least May 3 due to the ongoing coronavirus situation. Schools had originally been scheduled to reopen as soon as April 20. Schools may reopen on Monday, May 4, but an additional extension of the closure beyond that date is possible.

LBUSD leadership made the decision to extend the closure after careful consultation with partnering agencies, including the Los Angeles County Office of Education. The foremost consideration in this decision was the health of everyone in local school communities and beyond.

During this extended closure, local schools will continue to provide meals and home learning opportunities. By the end of the day on Monday, March 23, LBUSD will be sending home learning opportunity information to LBUSD students and their families. (Please visit lbschools.net for more info/ Also available in Spanish and Khmer)
